- Where are you going?

1189
01:42:29,936 --> 01:42:32,564
- All right!
- Now come on, motherfuckers!

1190
01:42:37,194 --> 01:42:39,655
Come on. You can do
better than that!

1191
01:42:39,738 --> 01:42:43,075
They just keep coming, man!
Fuck this shit!

1192
01:42:44,910 --> 01:42:47,204
Get back here, you gutless shit!

1193
01:43:46,471 --> 01:43:47,824
All right. Get me Bravo.
Right away.

1194
01:43:47,848 --> 01:43:49,742
Charlie Company reports
hand-to-hand on perimeter, sir.

1195
01:43:49,766 --> 01:43:51,685
Three holes are down.
They need help.

1196
01:43:51,768 --> 01:43:55,063
Okay. Get two squads from Alpha
down there right away. Go. Go.

1197
01:43:55,147 --> 01:43:57,149
Where's that goddamn air strike?

1198
01:43:58,650 --> 01:44:01,319
Hey, stupid, where the fuck you going?

1199
01:44:08,994 --> 01:44:10,454
Eagle Six...

1200
01:44:16,168 --> 01:44:17,669
Son of a bitch.

1201
01:44:20,213 --> 01:44:21,381
Can't you get anybody?

1202
01:44:21,465 --> 01:44:23,508
Damn it! Negative contact!
Can't raise Barnes.

1203
01:44:23,592 --> 01:44:25,177
Two Bravo, Two Charlie, nothing.

1204
01:44:25,260 --> 01:44:26,261
Get me Six!

1205
01:44:26,344 --> 01:44:28,930
Bravo Six! Bravo Six! Oh, God!

1206
01:44:30,265 --> 01:44:31,641
Get him in!

1207
01:44:35,520 --> 01:44:38,023
They're coming through all over!
I can't do anything!

1208
01:44:38,106 --> 01:44:39,232
Where's Barnes?

1209
01:44:39,357 --> 01:44:41,359
Shit, he's dead! I think
they're all dead.

1210
01:44:41,443 --> 01:44:44,696
Doc, he's dead. Six, LT, Six.

1211
01:44:45,030 --> 01:44:48,366
Captain. Captain, we've been overrun.
We're pulling back! Over.

1212
01:44:48,450 --> 01:44:51,578
God damn it, Lieutenant. Where
are you gonna pull back to?

1213
01:44:51,661 --> 01:44:53,622
They're all over the perimeter.

1214
01:44:53,705 --> 01:44:57,751
Now you be advised. You will hold
in place, and you will fight.

1215
01:44:57,834 --> 01:45:00,545
That means you, Lieutenant.
Bravo Six out.

1216
01:45:30,700 --> 01:45:32,911
Be advised. We've got zips
in the wire down here.

1217
01:45:32,994 --> 01:45:35,956
<i>Roger your last, Bravo Six.
Can't run it any closer.</i>

1218
01:45:36,081 --> 01:45:40,168
<i>We're hot to trot and packing snake
and nape but we're bingo on fuel.</i>

1219
01:45:40,252 --> 01:45:42,295
For the record, it's my call.

1220
01:45:42,337 --> 01:45:45,131
Dump everything you've got left on my pos.

1221
01:45:45,215 --> 01:45:49,553
I say again, expend all
remaining in my perimeter.

1222
01:45:50,095 --> 01:45:52,931
It's a lovely fucking war.
Bravo Six out.

1223
01:45:55,267 --> 01:45:58,687
<i>Roger your last, Bravo Six.
We copy. It's your call.</i>

1224
01:45:58,770 --> 01:46:02,023
<i>Get them in their holes down there.
Hang tough, Bravo Six.</i>

1225
01:46:02,107 --> 01:46:04,568
<i>We're coming cocked for treetops.</i>

1226
01:46:28,508 --> 01:46:29,759
Barnes!

1227
01:46:32,637 --> 01:46:33,889
Barnes!

1228
01:46:37,559 --> 01:46:39,561
No!

1229
01:49:29,647 --> 01:49:31,107
Get me a medic.

1230
01:49:34,027 --> 01:49:35,403
Go on, boy!

1231
01:49:53,588 --> 01:49:54,798
Do it.

1232
01:50:26,454 --> 01:50:29,332
We got men wounded and
live gooks at 3 o'clock.

1233
01:50:30,166 --> 01:50:32,544
Look down here.
Check them out.

1234
01:50:34,087 --> 01:50:36,881
Come on, Elmo. Move
your flea-bitten ass!

1235
01:50:40,677 --> 01:50:44,222
Hey, you okay? You all right?

1236
01:50:44,556 --> 01:50:46,683
Can you walk, huh?

1237
01:50:47,725 --> 01:50:52,021
Hey, Doc, we need a medic up here.
Come on, Elmo.

1238
01:50:52,105 --> 01:50:54,524
Come on, Doc, we got wounded here.

1239
01:51:13,459 --> 01:51:16,129
Yeah. That must have
been some fucking fight.

1240
01:51:17,422 --> 01:51:18,923
You alone here, man?

1241
01:51:19,966 --> 01:51:21,009
Yeah.

1242
01:51:21,926 --> 01:51:25,013
The bunch of fucking
faggots, they all left me.

1243
01:52:13,645 --> 01:52:17,398
122 wounded and still counting.

1244
01:52:17,482 --> 01:52:20,735
Estimate 500 Victor Charlie KIA.

1245
01:52:20,818 --> 01:52:23,947
122 and still counting. Over.

1246
01:52:30,411 --> 01:52:33,748
- Hey, Taylor, that you?
- Hey, Francis.

1247
01:52:33,831 --> 01:52:37,001
- Hey, man, how you doing?
- I'm okay. How you doing?

1248
01:52:37,168 --> 01:52:39,254
Fine, man. Just fine.
Hey, dig it.

1249
01:52:39,337 --> 01:52:41,923
We two timers, man. We're
gonna get out of here, boy.

1250
01:52:42,006 --> 01:52:46,135
I'm gonna see you in the hospital.
We gonna get high, high. Yes, sir.

1251
01:52:46,219 --> 01:52:47,845
Sergeant O'Neill.

1252
01:52:49,222 --> 01:52:51,307
- How you doing?
- Well, I'm just fine, sir.

1253
01:52:51,391 --> 01:52:54,560
Well, that's good. 'Cause
you got second platoon.

1254
01:52:55,019 --> 01:52:56,229
Yes, sir.

1255
01:53:06,322 --> 01:53:08,074
- You ready?
- You bet.

1256
01:54:37,163 --> 01:54:39,916
<i>I think now, looking back,</i>

1257
01:54:40,875 --> 01:54:44,796
<i>we did not fight the enemy.
We fought ourselves.</i>

1258
01:54:45,004 --> 01:54:47,548
<i>And the enemy was in us.</i>

1259
01:54:49,675 --> 01:54:51,761
<i>The war is over for me now,</i>

1260
01:54:51,969 --> 01:54:55,640
<i>but it will always be
there the rest of my days</i>

1261
01:54:56,474 --> 01:54:58,601
<i>as I'm sure Elias will be,</i>

1262
01:54:58,976 --> 01:55:02,897
<i>fighting with Barnes for what Rhah
called possession of my soul.</i>

1263
01:55:04,732 --> 01:55:06,317
<i>There are times since,</i>

1264
01:55:06,401 --> 01:55:10,029
<i>I've felt like the child
born of those two fathers.</i>

1265
01:55:13,157 --> 01:55:15,118
<i>But, be that as it may,</i>

1266
01:55:15,326 --> 01:55:17,078
<i>those of us who did make it</i>

1267
01:55:17,161 --> 01:55:19,497
<i>have an obligation to build again,</i>

1268
01:55:20,164 --> 01:55:22,458
<i>to teach to others what we know,</i>

1269
01:55:23,418 --> 01:55:26,170
<i>and to try with what's left of our lives</i>

1270
01:55:26,295 --> 01:55:29,757
<i>to find a goodness and
meaning to this life.</i>

